      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): wait for compaction cleanup before unsubscribing to prevent event loss [AI]",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n**Problem**: When agent execution times out (e.g., after 48h), the `unsubscribe()` function was calling `abortCompaction()` followed immediately by `sessionUnsubscribe()`. This created a race condition where the SDK's `auto_compaction_end` event might be emitted after the event listener was removed, causing the frontend to never receive the compaction end event.\r\n\r\n**What changed**:\r\n- Modified `unsubscribe()` to be async and wait for compaction cleanup\r\n- Added `waitForCompactionCleanup()` helper with 5s timeout\r\n- Added `compactionCleanupResolve` to state\r\n\r\n**Testing**:\r\n- Added 4 unit tests\r\n- All tests pass\r\n- Build passes\r\n\r\n@jalehman ",
